As he daydreamed, a strong hand pulled him up. Parna saw Uncle Teteyo and remembered, “Uncle, where are the cows?”
Uncle Teteyo replied, “Your mother found all the cows in the shed, except Blackie, and you. She was afraid so she sent me to fetch you.”
Parna excitedly told his uncle how Blackie gave birth to the beautiful calf. Uncle Teteyo said, “I'll carry the calf as you and Blackie follow.”
Everyone was happy to see Parna, Blackie and the calf safe.
